  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "TAX ACCOUNTANT",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>- Responsible for overall tax compliance matters including corporate income tax, withholding tax, etc.</p>\n<p>- Prepare/review the annual tax returns and ensure compliance to tax laws and regulations</p>\n<p>- Prepare/review the monthly corporate tax provision and tax accounting reporting (ie. deferred tax computation)</p>\n<p>- Conduct tax research and assist in identifying tax planning ideas and improvement opportunities</p>\n<p>- Liaise with various competent authorities in respect of the tax related queries/issues &amp; audits</p>\n<p>- Advise and provide support as and when required on the tax compliance and implication</p>\n<p>- Review and advise tax related contract clause including new project tendering, procurement contract and etc.</p>\n<p>- Keep abreast on the latest development of new legislation and tax updates and advise for full compliance</p>\n<p>- Other ad-hoc duties/tasks to be assigned as and when required.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirement</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>- 1-2 years of experience in taxation, customs and finance</p>\n<p>- Professional experience in taxation with Audit / Tax firms preferred</p>\n<p>- Tax Consultancy background preferred</p>\n<p>- A graduate of Business or Accounting is desirable</p>\n<p>- Proficient in Excel</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>5 days work</p>\n<p>10am - 7pm.</p>",
